You have found out that the sun works on the basis of the same principles as other stars: It was found that the activity of all stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation and nothing else.
To determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma current, the luminosity and the rotation are taken into account together.
Je kleiner die Rossby-Zahl ist, umso weniger aktiv ist der Stern in Bezug auf Umpolungen des Magnetfelds.
